          "Did you attend earnings calls in a support capacity — e.g., take notes, manage Q&A queues, coordinate analyst dial-ins?",
          "Which press release or earnings announcement had the most coordination weight from you?",
          "Would the IR manager you worked with be a reference today? What's their current title?",
        ],
      },
      {
        headline: "Managed a high-friction General Counsel relationship (bi-weekly ELT meeting coordination)",
        quote:
          "\"It did save us time and money, because I was still able to take on a lot of the coordination, updating of the spreadsheet, sending out the agenda, following up with the SLT members that he didn't have to do.\"",
        confidence: "Confirmed (qualitative)",
        questions: [
          "How many total meetings did you coordinate around him — weekly, bi-weekly, over how many months?",
          "What time savings for the GC's desk can you credibly estimate — hours per week, or a specific recovered work block?",
          "Did the CEO ever thank you explicitly for holding that dynamic together? If so, what did he say?",
          "What's the one behavioral pattern you learned about the GC that no one else on the ELT picked up on?",
          "In a behavioral interview, is this your \"tell me about a difficult colleague\" story? If yes, what's the 90-second version?",
        ],
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    id: "ascend-ach",
    role: "Ascend Wellness Holdings",
    achievements: [
      {
        headline: "Rebuilt earnings-call prep into a repeatable 6–8 week system after one cycle in-role",
        quote:
          "\"My new system came about in July last year after that was our q1 earnings.\"",
        confidence: "Confirmed",
        questions: [
          "How many hours of rework did the new system eliminate per earnings cycle — 10? 40?",
          "How many fewer back-and-forths between Mattio and the internal team did it produce?",
          "What was the single biggest Q4/Q1 pain point the new system solved — script freeze? presentation ownership? calendar alignment?",
          "Did the CFO or President ever explicitly credit the system improvement in a review or debrief?",
          "Is there a version of this system document (SharePoint, Notion, Word) you can export as a case-study artifact?",
        ],
      },
      {
        headline: "7-state operational coverage (NJ, PA, IL, MA, MD + MI + OH per dossier)",
        quote:
          "\"The seven markets. Was the seven states that we had operations in.\"",
        confidence: "Confirmed",
        questions: [
          "How many corporate (non-retail) stakeholders did you coordinate with across those 7 states in a typical month?",
          "Was there a state where the ops team was materially different in rhythm (e.g., earlier earnings input, different legal cadence)?",
          "Did you ever travel to one of the markets physically? If so, for what kind of meeting?",
          "Which state had the highest-stakes ops issues landing on your desk?",
          "For a resume bullet, what's the cleaner framing — \"coordinated across 7 states\" or \"coordinated a 46-location public cannabis operator\"?",
        ],
      },
      {
        headline: "Established quarterly board meetings from zero → planned 12 months of 2026 board + committee calendar in September 2025",
        quote:
          "\"When I came in, they didn't even have board meetings on the calendar… in September 2025 I started working on board meeting, board and committee meetings for the whole year of 2026.\"",
        confidence: "Confirmed",
        questions: [
          "How long did each board meeting take to prep before vs. after you standardized the cadence?",
          "What was the first board meeting like — did anything visibly improve at the second one that you'd attribute to your coordination?",
          "Were the board members explicitly appreciative of the 12-month forward calendar? Any direct quote you could cite?",
          "Did the forward-calendar approach reduce rescheduling friction (count of reschedules per quarter)?",
          "For a resume, what's stronger — \"established quarterly board meeting cadence\" or \"planned full-year board calendar 12 months ahead\"? Both are true; which lands best for a strategic-partnership-EA role?",
        ],
      },
      {
        headline: "8-person board governance (4 external directors + 4 executives) + Audit and Compensation committees",
        quote:
          "\"Four board members… four Ascend employees. I would attend the board meeting, the CEO, the CFO, the President and the Chief Counsel.\"",
        confidence: "Confirmed",
        questions: [
          "How often did the Audit committee and the Compensation committee each meet in 2025?",
          "Were you in the room for the committee meetings, or just coordinating around them?",
          "What was the most sensitive piece of information you were trusted with around those committees?",
          "Which of the 4 external directors was most engaged with you day-to-day (beyond the chairman)?",
          "Were you ever asked to suggest an agenda item or flag a governance gap? If so, did leadership act on it?",
        ],
      },
      {
        headline: "M&A weekly meeting participation — built follow-up dashboard + presentation mock-ups",
        quote:
          "\"Sam said to me they wanted more executive presence in the meetings… I made some mock ups of not only how best we could showcase the capture of the information… a dashboard of the follow up items.\"",
        confidence: "Confirmed",
        questions: [
          "How many M&A deals were in-flight at peak? Even a rough number (\"15–20 active deals\") sharpens the bullet.",
          "Did any of the mock-ups/dashboards get adopted officially, or did the Director of M&A stick with his informal approach?",
          "What was the one deal where your follow-up tracking demonstrably kept a thread alive that would have otherwise dropped?",
          "Did you ever see a deal close that you'd credit partly to your coordination? (Even a \"10% contribution\" framing.)",
          "Would the Director of M&A speak positively about your work today? Or is that a relationship that soured?",
        ],
      },
      {
        headline: "Chairman of the board gave her his personal phone number — direct text access",
        quote:
          "\"The chairman of the board, where he gave me his, his phone number. We were text messaging all the time.\"",
        confidence: "Confirmed",
        questions: [
          "Roughly how many texts per week at peak — once a month? Weekly? Daily?",
          "What kind of things did he text you about — logistics confirmations, off-agenda questions, sentiment checks?",
          "Would he be a willing reference today? Even a short quote would be extraordinary signal for a strategic-EA pitch.",
          "Did any other Ascend leader (CEO, CFO, President) know the chairman was texting you directly? How did they react?",
          "This is a rare trust signal — is it already in your resume or LinkedIn? If not, why not?",
        ],
      },
      {
        headline: "98% stakeholder satisfaction rate (self-estimate, consulting-proposal claim)",
        quote:
          "\"It's my estimate. And again, my evidence was the efficiency, the effectiveness, the messages that I got from not only the ELT, but also the chairman of the board.\"",
        confidence: "Estimated (her own admission)",
        questions: [
          "Is there any chance the stat was ever formally surveyed — an internal pulse, an HR check-in, a board feedback form? Worth a final look before the consulting proposal goes wider.",
          "If it stays an estimate, what's the honest reframing — \"consistent positive stakeholder feedback from ELT and board\"?",
          "Name the top 3 stakeholders whose satisfaction you'd stake your reputation on — and would they confirm if asked?",
          "Were there any stakeholders whose satisfaction dipped during your tenure? Understanding the 2% matters for defensibility.",
          "If you replace \"98%\" with a narrative (3 specific stakeholder quotes), does that land stronger in the proposal?",
        ],
      },
    ],
  },
];
---

<Layout title="Intake Research — Leigh-Ann Martin (Private)">
  <Header />
  <main>
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="pt-28 pb-16 md:pt-32 md:pb-20 bg-cream">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-secondary mb-4">
          Private — For Leigh-Ann + Izzy only
        </p>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-primary leading-tight mb-6">
          Intake research: twelve transcripts, twenty years, one brag sheet.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
          Every transcript you recorded through Otter has been summarized role by role. Every quantified achievement has been extracted with a source attribution, a confidence label, and a set of drill-down questions designed to pressure-test each number before it goes onto a resume, a LinkedIn profile, or a consulting proposal.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How to read this -->
    <section class="py-14 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-secondary mb-4">How to read this page</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-primary leading-tight mb-8">Three labels you'll see everywhere.</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <div class="bg-cream rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Confirmed</p>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Number or fact stated verbatim in the source transcript. Safe to use in resume, LinkedIn, proposals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-cream rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Estimated</p>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Self-estimate or carried-forward claim. Fine in conversation; flag the assumption if pressed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-cream rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Follow-up needed</p>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Topic raised, no metric stated. Answer one of the drill-down questions and it becomes Confirmed.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Transcript summaries -->
    <section id="transcripts" class="py-20 md:py-24 bg-warm">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="mb-12" data-reveal>
          <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-secondary mb-4">Part 1</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-primary leading-tight mb-4">
            Transcript summaries — role by role.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            One card per otter.ai transcript. Each card shows the role, tenure, narrative summary, and the signal strength for quantified achievements.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          {transcripts.map((t) => (
            <article id={t.id} class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8" data-reveal>
              <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-baseline md:justify-between gap-1 mb-2">
                <h3 class="font-serif text-xl md:text-2xl text-primary leading-snug">{t.company}</h3>
                <p class="text-[11px] font-mono text-text-muted tracking-tight">{t.file}</p>
              </div>
              <p class="text-secondary text-sm font-medium mb-1">{t.roleSubtitle}</p>
              <p class="text-text-muted text-xs mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide">{t.tenure}</p>
              <p class="text-text leading-relaxed mb-4">{t.narrative}</p>
              <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase text-text-muted">
                Signal: <span class="text-primary/80 normal-case tracking-normal font-medium">{t.signal}</span>
              </p>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Quantified achievements + drill-down questions -->
    <section id="achievements" class="py-20 md:py-24 bg-cream">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="mb-12" data-reveal>
          <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-secondary mb-4">Part 2</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-primary leading-tight mb-4">
            Quantified achievements, with questions to make them bulletproof.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            Every confirmed or estimated achievement from the transcripts, plus 4–5 drill-down questions per achievement. The questions are designed to either sharpen the metric (turn an estimate into a confirmed number) or unlock a STAR-ready story behind it. Answer a few before our next session and your brag sheet gets noticeably stronger.
          </p>
        </div>

        {achievementSections.map((section) => (
          <div id={section.id} class="mb-12" data-reveal>
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-primary leading-snug mb-6 border-l-4 border-secondary pl-4">
              {section.role}
            </h3>
            <div class="space-y-6">
              {section.achievements.map((ach) => (
                <article class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8">
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-3">
                    <span class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase text-white bg-secondary px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
                      {ach.confidence}
                    </span>
                  </div>
                  <p class="font-serif text-lg text-primary leading-snug mb-3">{ach.headline}</p>
                  <blockquote class="text-text-muted text-sm italic border-l-2 border-primary/10 pl-4 mb-5 leading-relaxed">
                    {ach.quote}
                  </blockquote>
                  <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-secondary mb-3">
                    Drill-down questions
                  </p>
                  <ol class="space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside text-text text-[15px] leading-relaxed marker:text-secondary marker:font-semibold">
                    {ach.questions.map((q) => (
                      <li>{q}</li>
                    ))}
                  </ol>
                </article>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Top 10 achievements to lead with -->
    <section class="py-20 md:py-24 bg-primary text-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="mb-10" data-reveal>
          <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-accent mb-4">Part 3</p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl leading-tight mb-4">
            The ten achievements to lead with.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-white/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            Confirmed only. Ranked by defensibility and signal-to-noise. These are the ones that walk into a final-round interview, a negotiation, or a pitch deck without flinching.
          </p>
        </div>

        <ol class="space-y-5 list-decimal list-outside ml-6 marker:text-accent marker:font-serif marker:text-xl" data-reveal>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Built the Immunovant EA function from zero; supported 5 C-suite execs as sole EA between Sept 2019 and March 2020 (CEO, GC, CMO, CFO, CTDO).
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Established quarterly board meetings at Ascend — none were on the calendar when she arrived — and planned the full 2026 board + committee calendar in September 2025 (12 months ahead).
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Co-founded the Immunovant Culture Committee (6–10 members, 6-month rotation) with charter aligned to company KPIs and post-event satisfaction surveys.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Rebuilt Ascend's earnings-call prep into a repeatable 6–8 week system after one cycle in-role; ran it for Q2 2025.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Supported two PwC tax teams simultaneously (Indirect Tax + State/Income Franchise Tax) across the full ladder from associate to MD, plus Thought Leadership MD for internal firm services.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Owned PwC's Thought Leadership WHIP workflow at <span class="text-accent">3 purchase orders × 500 companies</span> scale — weekly maintenance + pivot-table analysis.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Coordinated Ascend's 8-person board (4 external directors + 4 executives) and 2 standing committees (Audit + Compensation).
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Built the Immunovant EA onboarding system (spreadsheet tabs + buddy pairings + weekly all-EA syncs) — pre-system ramp was 6–8 weeks.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Coordinated FDA meeting prep for a pre-IPO biopharma — CEO + CMO + General Counsel readiness, fireproof lockbox for hardcopy FDA correspondence, ad-board coordination.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="pl-2">
            <p class="text-white font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Authored an EA-function onboarding manual at Third Bridge covering office-manager backup, travel/expense policy, external-guest protocols, and President/CEO NY-visit playbook.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What's next -->
    <section class="py-20 md:py-24 bg-warm">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 text-center" data-reveal>
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-secondary mb-4">Next</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-primary leading-tight mb-6">
          Pick five drill-down questions. Answer them before Session 2.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
          You don't need to answer all 100-plus questions on this page. The five that matter most are the ones tied to your top three target roles. Answer those, and the brag sheet becomes the sharpest version of your career every recruiter and hiring manager will meet.
        </p>
        <a
          href="#achievements"
          class="inline-block bg-secondary text-white px-7 py-3 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-secondary/90 transition-all"
        >
          Jump to the questions
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<script>
  const revealEls = document.querySelectorAll("[data-reveal], [data-reveal-stagger]");
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add("revealed");
          observer.unobserve(entry.target);
        }
      });
    },
    { threshold: 0.1, rootMargin: "0px 0px -60px 0px" }
  );
  revealEls.forEach((el) => observer.observe(el));
</script>
